# 🏥 Behavioral Health Treatment Prediction using Machine Learning

## 📌 Overview

This project focuses on predicting whether individuals are likely to seek mental health treatment based on demographic, behavioral, and workplace-related factors. The objective is to leverage machine learning techniques to identify significant predictors that support healthcare professionals and organizations in making data-driven decisions.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- Analyze behavioral health survey data.
- Perform data cleaning and preprocessing.
- Build predictive machine learning models.
- Evaluate model performance using standard metrics.
- Visualize insights using interactive dashboards.

---

## 📊 Dataset

The project uses a publicly available behavioral health survey dataset containing demographic information, workplace conditions, family history, and mental health indicators.

